== Equality ==

Equality is an equivalence relation for numbers. Natural number equality is derived from the
[/wiki/peano/arithmetic/axioms | Peano axioms]. Natural number equality is used to
[/wiki/peano/arithmetic/integers | construct integer equality]. Integer equality is used to 
[/wiki/peano/arithmetic/rationals | construct rational equality].

=== Essential Properties ===

* Reflexive: #(= a a)# ([/edit/peano_new/predicate/equality_min.ghi/eqid | natural], [/edit/peano_new/arithmetic/integers/equality_min.gh/eqid | integer], [/edit/peano_new/arithmetic/rationals/NaN_construction/equality_min.gh/eqid | rational])
* Symmetric: #(<-> (= a b) (= b a))# ([/edit/peano_new/predicate/equality_min.ghi/eqcom | natural], [/edit/peano_new/arithmetic/integers/equality_min.gh/eqcom | integer], [/edit/peano_new/arithmetic/rationals/NaN_construction/equality_min.gh/eqcom | rational])
* Transitive: #(-> (/\ (= a b) (= a b)) (= b c))# ([/edit/peano_new/predicate/equality_min.ghi/eqtr | natural], [/edit/peano_new/arithmetic/integers/equality_min.gh/eqtr | integer], [/edit/peano_new/arithmetic/rationals/NaN_construction/equality_min.gh/eqtr | rational])
* Existence: #(E. x (= x A))# ([/edit/peano_new/predicate/equality_min.ghi/tyex | natural], [/edit/peano_new/arithmetic/integers/equality_min.gh/tyex | integer], [/edit/peano_new/arithmetic/rationals/NaN_construction/equality_min.gh/tyex | rational])

